WEBVTT

00:00:01.520 --> 00:00:04.519
Greetings, brothers and sisters.

00:00:04.519 --> 00:00:08.320
Welcome to this special edition of JW Broadcasting,

00:00:08.320 --> 00:00:12.919
originating from the World Headquarters of Jehovah's Witnesses.

00:00:12.919 --> 00:00:20.559
Our programs this month and next will feature the entire regional convention program for 2020.

00:00:20.559 --> 00:00:26.640
Although the COVID-19 pandemic has resulted in cancellations of gatherings around the world,

00:00:26.640 --> 00:00:32.979
Jehovah continues to provide spiritual food at the proper time.

00:00:32.979 --> 00:00:40.179
At the time this program was recorded, local governments had already mandated social distancing.

00:00:40.179 --> 00:00:45.979
In compliance, we filmed the entire convention program without an audience,

00:00:45.979 --> 00:00:50.649
and we are pleased to present it to you now.

00:00:50.649 --> 00:00:57.350
In behalf of the governing body and all the brothers and sisters working unitedly here at World Headquarters,

00:00:57.350 --> 00:01:04.549
it's my pleasure to extend to every one of you a very warm welcome.

00:01:04.549 --> 00:01:10.250
Our convention program this year has, as its theme, always rejoice,

00:01:10.250 --> 00:01:14.849
and our theme scripture for this opening day is Philippians 4-4.

00:01:14.849 --> 00:01:21.049
Always rejoice in the Lord, again I will say rejoice.

00:01:21.049 --> 00:01:26.349
This first session of our convention begins with a music video presentation.

00:01:26.349 --> 00:01:32.900
This video highlights the joy we experience when we gather together for worship.

00:01:32.900 --> 00:01:37.700
If you have with you a cellular telephone or other electronic device,

00:01:37.700 --> 00:01:41.799
please adjust it to a setting that will not disturb others.

00:01:41.799 --> 00:01:44.900
And now please enjoy the presentation.

00:02:06.390 --> 00:11:56.879
We are delighted that you could join us for this opening session of the Always Rejoice Convention of Jehovah's Witnesses.

00:11:56.980 --> 00:12:04.480
Please stand as we sing together song number 111 entitled Our Reasons for Joy.

00:12:04.480 --> 00:12:09.679
After the song, you may pause the program for your local opening prayer.

00:12:09.679 --> 00:14:35.679
Again, that song number 111, please be seated.

00:14:35.679 --> 00:14:40.279
Is it realistic for us to rejoice at all times?

00:14:40.279 --> 00:14:44.840
If so, how is it possible?

00:14:44.840 --> 00:14:50.639
Please pay careful attention to Brother Kenneth Cook, a member of the governing body of Jehovah's Witnesses.

00:14:50.639 --> 00:14:54.840
As he directs attention to our source of joy in the talk,

00:14:54.840 --> 00:15:04.570
why Jehovah is the happy God?

00:15:04.570 --> 00:15:12.169
Welcome to the 2020 Always Rejoice Regional Convention of Jehovah's Witnesses.

00:15:12.169 --> 00:15:19.370
From the start, we wish to convey to you greetings from the governing body and the entire Bethel family.

00:15:19.370 --> 00:15:24.669
And we want you to know that we love you and we keep you in our prayers.

00:15:24.669 --> 00:15:29.269
So now, whether you are watching this from home or from some other location,

00:15:29.269 --> 00:15:34.070
this is our convention for 2020.

00:15:34.070 --> 00:15:36.169
And what an encouraging theme.

00:15:36.169 --> 00:15:38.269
Always rejoice.

00:15:38.269 --> 00:15:43.669
We need to discuss this subject now more than ever before, don't we?

00:15:43.669 --> 00:15:47.970
Is it possible to rejoice as the world crumbles around us?

00:15:47.970 --> 00:15:49.470
Yes, it is.

00:15:49.470 --> 00:15:54.269
Those who love Jehovah can always find reasons to rejoice.

00:15:54.269 --> 00:15:59.970
Throughout this convention, we will discuss four things that will help us to rejoice.

00:15:59.970 --> 00:16:01.669
What are they?

00:16:01.669 --> 00:16:06.669
Number one, we will consider the reasons we have for rejoicing.

00:16:06.669 --> 00:16:11.269
Two, we will examine how we can cultivate godly joy.

00:16:11.269 --> 00:16:16.070
Three, we will look at how we can maintain joy despite trials.

00:16:16.169 --> 00:16:20.169
And four, we will discuss how to express joy.

00:16:20.169 --> 00:16:24.669
That is the joy we receive from serving Jehovah.

00:16:24.669 --> 00:16:30.169
Now, let's lay the foundation for all of this by first answering the question,

00:16:30.169 --> 00:16:33.169
what is true joy?

00:16:33.169 --> 00:16:38.970
What is commonly called joy is an emotion that is stirred by a feeling of well-being,

00:16:38.970 --> 00:16:44.169
by a sense of success, or because of expecting something good.

00:16:44.169 --> 00:16:50.669
And for this reason, joy may seem to come and go depending on what is happening around us.

00:16:50.669 --> 00:16:54.269
You might call it circumstantial joy,

00:16:54.269 --> 00:16:56.870
but that is not the case with true joy.

00:16:56.870 --> 00:16:58.269
Why?

00:16:58.269 --> 00:17:05.569
Because true joy, godly joy, is an aspect of the fruitage of God's Holy Spirit.

00:17:05.569 --> 00:17:12.769
True joy is a quality of the heart that is not dependent on external things happening around us.

00:17:12.869 --> 00:17:16.970
This godly quality comes from knowing that you have the truth,

00:17:16.970 --> 00:17:19.670
that you are doing what pleases God,

00:17:19.670 --> 00:17:23.569
and that your kingdom hope is certain to be fulfilled.

00:17:23.569 --> 00:17:29.069
So then, we see there's a big difference between having circumstantial joy

00:17:29.069 --> 00:17:32.069
and having joy of Holy Spirit.

00:17:32.069 --> 00:17:38.269
This is illustrated for us in the Scriptures by the example of the Christians in Thessalonica.

00:17:38.269 --> 00:17:41.970
The Apostle Paul and others helped them to prepare ahead of time

00:17:41.970 --> 00:17:47.269
to face persecution with joy and prepare they did.

00:17:47.269 --> 00:17:48.269
How?

00:17:48.269 --> 00:17:51.670
They became strong in faith.

00:17:51.670 --> 00:17:58.470
Let's read about what this did for them at first Thessalonians chapter 1 and verse 6.

00:17:58.470 --> 00:18:01.269
As we read the verse, ask yourself,

00:18:01.269 --> 00:18:04.769
where did their deep-seated joy come from?

00:18:04.769 --> 00:18:06.470
The verse reads,

00:18:35.569 --> 00:18:47.170
Godly joy is not a mere personality trait that we are born with then, is it?

00:18:47.170 --> 00:18:51.970
And it doesn't come to us simply because of pleasant circumstances.

00:18:51.970 --> 00:18:56.069
Joy of Holy Spirit is found deep within us,

00:18:56.069 --> 00:19:01.470
and so it should not be confused with simply being cheerful or exuberant.

00:19:01.470 --> 00:19:04.369
Godly joy is not superficial.

00:19:04.369 --> 00:19:10.369
It's not found in constantly smiling or laughing to show the difference.

00:19:10.369 --> 00:19:14.369
Think of a comedian who seems to be able to find what is funny

00:19:14.369 --> 00:19:17.569
in just about any situation in life.

00:19:17.569 --> 00:19:22.769
Yet deep down inside, he may be very unhappy.

00:19:22.769 --> 00:19:26.470
In contrast, like the Christians in Thessalonica,

00:19:26.470 --> 00:19:32.069
we can have joy of Holy Spirit even when we are under tribulation.

00:19:32.170 --> 00:19:34.769
We may not smile through a bad time,

00:19:34.769 --> 00:19:39.769
but our deep inner joy in serving Jehovah is immovable.

00:19:39.769 --> 00:19:46.670
It's part of the new personality that true Christians put on in order to be like Christ.

00:19:46.670 --> 00:19:51.170
Now, with this basic understanding of Godly joy in mind,

00:19:51.170 --> 00:19:54.369
let's give our attention to Brother Stephen Let,

00:19:54.369 --> 00:20:01.170
a member of the governing body as he welcomes us to this always rejoice convention.

00:20:01.269 --> 00:20:10.119
And please listen carefully as he explains why Godly joy is such a special quality.

00:20:10.119 --> 00:20:18.119
Welcome to the always rejoice convention of Jehovah's Witnesses.

00:20:18.119 --> 00:20:26.319
We're so happy that you were able to arrange to attend all three days of this convention.

00:20:26.420 --> 00:20:31.119
Why were the Apostle Paul's words at Philippians 4.4

00:20:31.119 --> 00:20:36.119
chosen as the theme for this year's convention?

00:20:36.119 --> 00:20:41.920
Well, over the past four years, the governing body has used conventions

00:20:41.920 --> 00:20:48.119
to highlight qualities that endear us to Jehovah

00:20:48.119 --> 00:20:56.119
and help us to be victorious in our struggle against Satan and his world.

00:20:56.420 --> 00:21:02.920
We've had convention themes that focused on the need for loyalty,

00:21:02.920 --> 00:21:11.420
endurance, courage, and love.

00:21:11.420 --> 00:21:17.420
This year, the convention theme highlights the need for joy.

00:21:17.519 --> 00:21:26.819
At Nehemiah 8.10, we're told the joy of Jehovah is your stronghold.

00:21:26.819 --> 00:21:33.619
In the near future, our faith will be tested as never before.

00:21:33.619 --> 00:21:38.420
But if we acquire true joy with the help of God's Holy Spirit,

00:21:38.420 --> 00:21:46.720
we will be able to stand firm and weather all the storms that come our way.

00:21:46.819 --> 00:21:52.019
Godly joy is a deep-seated quality of the heart.

00:21:52.019 --> 00:22:00.519
It's a state of happiness that remains whether the conditions around us are pleasant or not.

00:22:00.519 --> 00:22:05.319
In fact, a person can be disturbed about something,

00:22:05.319 --> 00:22:10.019
but still have joy in his heart.

00:22:10.019 --> 00:22:15.720
For example, the Apostles were flogged for speaking about the Christ.

00:22:15.819 --> 00:22:20.319
Yet they went out from before the Sanadran rejoicing

00:22:20.319 --> 00:22:27.319
because they had been counted worthy to be dishonored in behalf of his name.

00:22:27.319 --> 00:22:33.119
Obviously, they weren't rejoicing over the flogging they had received,

00:22:33.119 --> 00:22:42.519
but as servants of God, they found true joy in keeping their integrity to him.

00:22:42.519 --> 00:22:49.920
However, is it possible for a Christian always to be rejoicing?

00:22:49.920 --> 00:22:58.220
Yes, because true joy is an aspect of the fruitage of God's Holy Spirit.

00:22:58.220 --> 00:23:04.819
As an inward quality, joy is not dependent on external things,

00:23:04.819 --> 00:23:11.619
not even on our brothers, but it does depend on God's Spirit.

00:23:11.619 --> 00:23:17.819
And as already noted, our joy comes from that deep inner satisfaction

00:23:17.819 --> 00:23:21.220
of knowing that we have the truth,

00:23:21.220 --> 00:23:24.220
that we're doing what pleases Jehovah,

00:23:24.220 --> 00:23:28.920
and that our kingdom hope is sure.

00:23:28.920 --> 00:23:34.720
So Godly joy is not the transient joy that people experience

00:23:34.720 --> 00:23:38.619
because they've secured a well-paying job.

00:23:38.619 --> 00:23:44.519
Gone on an exotic vacation, attained fame and prestige,

00:23:44.519 --> 00:23:50.619
or acquired some coveted material item, or large sum of money.

00:23:50.619 --> 00:23:52.220
No.

00:23:52.220 --> 00:23:58.519
True joy has to be cultivated by means of Holy Spirit.

00:23:58.519 --> 00:24:02.720
To obtain Jehovah's Holy Spirit, we have to draw close to him

00:24:02.720 --> 00:24:06.420
and give him exclusive devotion.

00:24:06.420 --> 00:24:11.819
At Acts 532, we're told that God gives Holy Spirit

00:24:11.819 --> 00:24:16.819
to those obeying him as ruler.

00:24:16.819 --> 00:24:20.920
During these three days, the convention program

00:24:20.920 --> 00:24:27.319
will help us to deepen our appreciation for Godly joy.

00:24:27.319 --> 00:24:32.720
We'll learn what true joy is, how to cultivate it,

00:24:32.720 --> 00:24:36.220
how to maintain it during difficult times

00:24:36.220 --> 00:24:42.019
and how to display it as it wells up in our hearts.

00:24:42.019 --> 00:24:48.119
Such joy will clearly identify us as disciples of Jesus,

00:24:48.119 --> 00:24:53.220
and it will enable us to serve as beacons of light

00:24:53.220 --> 00:24:59.920
in this dark world and draw others to our happy God.

00:24:59.920 --> 00:25:03.519
You'll note that nearly the entire second day

00:25:03.519 --> 00:25:09.119
has been devoted to the joy of disciple making.

00:25:09.119 --> 00:25:14.319
Godly joy will help us to face challenges to our integrity.

00:25:14.319 --> 00:25:18.019
Remember that it was the joy that was set before him

00:25:18.019 --> 00:25:24.920
that helped Jesus to face an excruciating death on a torture stake.

00:25:24.920 --> 00:25:29.819
So please pay rapt attention to the talks and videos.

00:25:29.819 --> 00:25:34.220
Look up the scriptures and read them along with the speakers.

00:25:34.220 --> 00:25:42.420
Thus allowing God's Word to exert its powerful force on your heart.

00:25:42.420 --> 00:25:47.619
May this convention become a milestone in your development

00:25:47.619 --> 00:25:53.619
as a joyful imitator of our happy God.

00:25:53.619 --> 00:25:58.819
How thankful we are that He made us in His image,

00:25:58.819 --> 00:26:05.119
giving us the capacity to feel and express Godly joy.

00:26:05.119 --> 00:26:10.119
And how thankful we are that He also gives us His Holy Spirit

00:26:10.119 --> 00:26:14.019
to help us cultivate that kind of joy.

00:26:14.019 --> 00:26:17.619
We love you very much,

00:26:17.619 --> 00:26:22.819
and we pray that each one of you will forever respond

00:26:22.819 --> 00:26:27.920
to the words of the Psalmist at Psalm 100 verse 2.

00:26:27.920 --> 00:26:31.920
Serve Jehovah with rejoicing.

00:26:31.920 --> 00:26:39.720
Come into His presence with joyful shouting.

00:26:39.720 --> 00:26:43.420
We wish to thank Brother Lead for building up our anticipation

00:26:43.420 --> 00:26:46.720
for this always rejoice convention.

00:26:46.720 --> 00:26:53.119
As Brother Lead highlighted, Godly joy is indeed a very special quality.

00:26:53.119 --> 00:26:56.420
Such true joy comes from Jehovah Himself.

00:26:56.420 --> 00:27:02.220
In fact, the Bible says that He always has reasons to rejoice.

00:27:02.220 --> 00:27:08.220
So much so that being happy describes His personality.

00:27:08.220 --> 00:27:14.220
Let's see this for ourselves as we read 1 Timothy chapter 1 and verse 11.

00:27:14.220 --> 00:27:19.220
The context in verses 8 through 10 lists many of the bad qualities

00:27:19.220 --> 00:27:22.519
and actions that people of this world display.

00:27:22.519 --> 00:27:28.119
But they can change if they listen to our joyful God Jehovah.

00:27:28.119 --> 00:27:33.420
With that in mind, note the Apostle Paul's inspired words in verse 11

00:27:33.420 --> 00:27:35.720
as he goes on to say,

00:27:35.720 --> 00:27:40.119
according to the glorious good news of the happy God

00:27:40.119 --> 00:27:43.519
with which I was entrusted.

00:27:43.519 --> 00:27:48.220
Why can Jehovah be called happy despite seeing all of the problems

00:27:48.220 --> 00:27:50.220
and suffering on the earth?

00:27:50.319 --> 00:27:55.619
Well, among the many things that may come happy are the following 4.

00:27:55.619 --> 00:27:58.319
1. Jehovah is the Creator.

00:27:58.319 --> 00:28:01.519
Everything He does is perfect.

00:28:01.519 --> 00:28:07.019
Due to Ronomy 32 and verse 4 says, perfect is His activity.

00:28:07.019 --> 00:28:11.819
For this reason, Jehovah can rightly rejoice in His creation.

00:28:11.819 --> 00:28:18.920
That fact is undeniable and it's clearly stated in Psalm 104 and verse 31.

00:28:19.019 --> 00:28:26.019
As we read it together, consider how determined Jehovah is to keep His joy.

00:28:26.019 --> 00:28:28.720
Verse 31 says,

00:28:28.720 --> 00:28:31.920
the glory of Jehovah will last forever.

00:28:31.920 --> 00:28:37.119
Jehovah will rejoice in His works.

00:28:37.119 --> 00:28:38.619
The point?

00:28:38.619 --> 00:28:40.119
Jehovah will not be denied.

00:28:40.119 --> 00:28:44.619
Well, he he will find joy in what he has accomplished.

00:28:44.619 --> 00:28:47.119
No one can take that from him.

00:28:47.119 --> 00:28:53.119
He's the happy God whose purpose for man and for the earth will be realized.

00:28:53.119 --> 00:28:56.920
Adding to His happiness is reason number 2.

00:28:56.920 --> 00:29:02.720
Jehovah is generous and we know what the Bible says about those who give.

00:29:02.720 --> 00:29:08.519
And aren't we grateful for all that Jehovah is providing to help us and support us now

00:29:08.519 --> 00:29:11.819
through a very difficult time?

00:29:11.920 --> 00:29:12.920
Number 3.

00:29:12.920 --> 00:29:17.720
Jehovah's heart is made glad by the faithfulness of His servants.

00:29:17.720 --> 00:29:21.220
He never forgets all that we have done.

00:29:21.220 --> 00:29:24.319
At Proverbs 23, 15, he says,

00:29:24.319 --> 00:29:26.720
if your heart becomes wise,

00:29:26.720 --> 00:29:30.519
then my own heart will rejoice.

00:29:30.519 --> 00:29:33.619
If we remain faithful to Jehovah,

00:29:33.619 --> 00:29:38.220
the joy that we can bring to Him will last forever.

00:29:38.220 --> 00:29:40.119
And number 4.

00:29:40.119 --> 00:29:42.319
Because Jehovah is perfect,

00:29:42.319 --> 00:29:44.619
He always does what is right.

00:29:44.619 --> 00:29:49.920
He will never do anything to spoil His own happiness.

00:29:49.920 --> 00:29:53.420
Well, now that we have looked at what makes Jehovah the happy God,

00:29:53.420 --> 00:29:56.220
we want to know what makes us happy.

00:29:56.220 --> 00:29:58.819
That is what makes us truly happy.

00:29:58.819 --> 00:30:01.920
Deep down inside happy.

00:30:01.920 --> 00:30:06.819
After all, it's not difficult to find superficial happiness.

00:30:06.819 --> 00:30:10.519
For instance, when you're near someone with a funny laugh,

00:30:10.519 --> 00:30:13.819
do you often find yourself laughing as well?

00:30:13.819 --> 00:30:15.420
It happens, right?

00:30:15.420 --> 00:30:18.920
You may not even know what you're laughing about, true?

00:30:18.920 --> 00:30:20.519
The point is this,

00:30:20.519 --> 00:30:25.920
it's not all that difficult to experience superficial happiness

00:30:25.920 --> 00:30:29.220
but to find lasting joy, takes effort,

00:30:29.220 --> 00:30:33.819
and it takes appreciation for what we have.

00:30:33.819 --> 00:30:38.619
We will now look at some of the things that bring us real joy.

00:30:38.619 --> 00:30:40.420
And as you might expect,

00:30:40.420 --> 00:30:43.519
it begins with Jehovah.

00:30:43.519 --> 00:30:49.720
Our relationship with Jehovah is our foremost reason for joy.

00:30:49.720 --> 00:30:52.119
But not just any relationship.

00:30:52.119 --> 00:30:59.519
Take note of what is needed as we read Psalm 16 and verse 11.

00:30:59.519 --> 00:31:03.519
As we do so first, notice what Jehovah does.

00:31:03.619 --> 00:31:07.819
Next, see what type of relationship we can have with him.

00:31:07.819 --> 00:31:11.819
Then, make the connection to having joy.

00:31:11.819 --> 00:31:16.019
Psalm 16 verse 11 reads,

00:31:16.019 --> 00:31:19.220
You make known to me the path of life.

00:31:19.220 --> 00:31:24.819
In your presence is abundant joy.

00:31:24.819 --> 00:31:28.019
So again, first, what does Jehovah do?

00:31:28.019 --> 00:31:31.720
He kindly makes the path of life known to us.

00:31:31.720 --> 00:31:36.220
Next, what type of relationship can we have with him?

00:31:36.220 --> 00:31:38.619
A very close one, it says,

00:31:38.619 --> 00:31:41.019
as if in his very presence.

00:31:41.019 --> 00:31:45.019
Then, we read that in his presence, there's what?

00:31:45.019 --> 00:31:48.019
Abundant joy.

00:31:48.019 --> 00:31:52.619
Now, along with having a close relationship with Jehovah,

00:31:52.619 --> 00:31:56.920
as mentioned there, what else brings us joy?

00:31:56.920 --> 00:31:59.119
Jehovah's Holy Spirit does.

00:31:59.119 --> 00:32:03.920
His Holy Spirit generates joy in those who receive it.

00:32:03.920 --> 00:32:08.619
For this reason, we should pray to receive his Holy Spirit every day.

00:32:08.619 --> 00:32:11.519
What else promotes true joy within us?

00:32:11.519 --> 00:32:13.720
Our marvelous hope.

00:32:13.720 --> 00:32:16.920
Also, we have an abundance of spiritual food,

00:32:16.920 --> 00:32:20.619
even under difficult circumstances.

00:32:20.619 --> 00:32:24.119
That joyful blessing was foretold in God's Word.

00:32:24.220 --> 00:32:31.420
To see it, please go to Isaiah chapter 65 and verses 13 and 14.

00:32:31.420 --> 00:32:33.720
Now, in these verses,

00:32:33.720 --> 00:32:37.019
Jehovah draws a contrast between good people

00:32:37.019 --> 00:32:43.470
and bad people when he says this starting in verse 13.

00:32:43.470 --> 00:32:47.170
Therefore, this is what the sovereign Lord Jehovah says.

00:32:47.170 --> 00:32:51.869
Look, my servants will eat, but you will go hungry.

00:32:51.869 --> 00:32:57.170
Look, my servants will drink, but you will go thirsty.

00:32:57.170 --> 00:33:02.470
Look, my servants will rejoice, but you will suffer shame.

00:33:02.470 --> 00:33:05.369
Look, my servants will shout joyfully

00:33:05.369 --> 00:33:08.470
because of the good condition of the heart,

00:33:08.470 --> 00:33:14.920
but you will cry out because of the pain of heart.

00:33:14.920 --> 00:33:19.420
Do you see yourself on Jehovah's side of this contrast?

00:33:19.420 --> 00:33:22.220
If you've been keeping up with God's organization,

00:33:22.220 --> 00:33:25.519
you should feel well fed spiritually.

00:33:25.519 --> 00:33:28.519
The bad conditions of this world must not be permitted

00:33:28.519 --> 00:33:31.019
to take away from our joy.

00:33:31.019 --> 00:33:33.420
As Jehovah said, we shall joyfully.

00:33:33.420 --> 00:33:34.420
Why?

00:33:34.420 --> 00:33:37.920
Because of the good condition of the heart.

00:33:37.920 --> 00:33:40.420
We are more ready than ever before

00:33:40.420 --> 00:33:43.619
to see the realization of our hope.

00:33:43.619 --> 00:33:45.220
On the other hand,

00:33:45.220 --> 00:33:47.720
the world around us is suffering

00:33:47.720 --> 00:33:50.819
because they lack clear direction

00:33:50.920 --> 00:33:53.720
and they are without real hope.

00:33:53.720 --> 00:33:57.619
Throughout our lives, and especially at times like this,

00:33:57.619 --> 00:34:01.220
we should take note of Jehovah's help.

00:34:01.220 --> 00:34:04.119
When we see that Jehovah is helping us,

00:34:04.119 --> 00:34:05.920
we know that he is with us.

00:34:05.920 --> 00:34:11.420
We just know it, and this too brings us immense joy.

00:34:11.420 --> 00:34:15.619
Also, we find joy in hearing the expressions of faith

00:34:15.619 --> 00:34:19.619
that come from our dear brothers and sisters, don't we?

00:34:19.719 --> 00:34:20.719
And this is true,

00:34:20.719 --> 00:34:23.820
whether we meet together for worship in person

00:34:23.820 --> 00:34:26.219
or whether we meet by means of video.

00:34:27.219 --> 00:34:31.519
In fact, with so much to add to our inner joy,

00:34:31.519 --> 00:34:34.119
we can come to have a joy so strong

00:34:34.119 --> 00:34:38.820
and so deep within us that nothing can shake it.

00:34:38.820 --> 00:34:42.519
Even persecution, though not enjoyable in itself,

00:34:42.519 --> 00:34:44.159
can lead to joy.

00:34:44.159 --> 00:34:45.820
How so?

00:34:45.920 --> 00:34:50.219
As Jesus said, at Matthew 5, 11 and 12,

00:34:50.219 --> 00:34:53.420
happy are you when people reproach you

00:34:53.420 --> 00:34:57.219
and persecute you and lyingly say every sort of wicked thing

00:34:57.219 --> 00:34:59.420
against you for my sake.

00:34:59.420 --> 00:35:04.920
Rejoice and be overjoyed since your reward is great.

00:35:04.920 --> 00:35:08.119
So how can we be joyful,

00:35:08.119 --> 00:35:10.420
even though we are persecuted

00:35:10.420 --> 00:35:14.519
because when we endure persecution with joy

00:35:14.619 --> 00:35:18.019
and keep our integrity, we gain a victory

00:35:18.019 --> 00:35:20.019
and Jehovah's approval.

00:35:20.019 --> 00:35:23.119
Jesus said, rejoice and be overjoyed

00:35:23.119 --> 00:35:25.320
since your reward is great.

00:35:26.820 --> 00:35:29.719
Well, so far we have defined true joy.

00:35:29.719 --> 00:35:33.719
We have examined why Jehovah is called the happy God

00:35:33.719 --> 00:35:35.519
and we have reviewed a number of things

00:35:35.519 --> 00:35:37.920
that bring us godly joy.

00:35:37.920 --> 00:35:40.119
