01:32:19.739 --> 01:32:27.739
And notice the kind of friendships we will enjoy when they are based on spiritual values.

01:32:27.739 --> 01:32:30.739
Proverbs 17, verse 17.

01:32:31.739 --> 01:32:40.739
A true friend shows love at all times, and is a brother who is born for times of distress.

01:32:40.739 --> 01:32:47.739
True friends support one another, physically, emotionally, and spiritually.

01:32:47.739 --> 01:32:53.739
And our true friendships make a valuable contribution to our joy.

01:32:53.739 --> 01:33:04.279
People everywhere want to be happy, but many fail to find true joy because they are looking in the wrong place.

01:33:04.279 --> 01:33:14.279
As we have discussed in this symposium, the world claims that we can be happy if we pursue wealth, if we engage in sinful conduct,

01:33:14.279 --> 01:33:22.279
if we adopt extreme views of work, or if we cultivate friendships anywhere we can find them.

01:33:23.279 --> 01:33:30.279
Such assertions originate with the ruler of the world, the father of the lie, Satan the devil.

01:33:30.279 --> 01:33:37.279
If we look for happiness in Satan's world, we are going to be disappointed.

01:33:37.279 --> 01:33:48.279
In contrast, this first symposium of our always rejoiced convention has identified four factors that contribute to our lasting joy.

01:33:48.279 --> 01:34:04.279
God's word teaches us that joy comes from first living a simple life, second having a clean conscience, third doing meaningful work, and fourth having true friendships.

01:34:04.279 --> 01:34:10.279
Our loving father, Jehovah, knows what makes us truly happy.

01:34:10.279 --> 01:34:14.279
So may we continue to follow his sound advice.

01:34:14.279 --> 01:34:20.279
If we do, we will find abundant joy that lasts forever.

01:34:20.279 --> 01:34:28.750
Thank you, brothers, for highlighting how God's word guides us to a way of life that is truly joyful.

